def: An extinct genus of huge vertebrates, probably dinosaurs, knownonly from four-toed tracks in Triassic sandstones.
One who produces, or offers to notice. [Obs.] Ayliffe.
A women who plays in comedy.
Of or pertaining to Morocco, or its inhabitants.

A heavy iron lever having an oscillating motion on a centralaxis, one end of which is connected with the piston rod from which itreceives motion, and the other with the crank of the wheel shaft; --called also working beam or walking beam.
Capable of being inhabited; habitable.Systems of inhabitable planets. Locke.
A genus of bulbous-rooted plants found in many parts of Europe,including the meadow saffron.
Having the jaws slightly projecting; between prognathous andorthognathous. See Gnathic index, under Gnathic.
